			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Amateur Trak Homework to be graded and corrected please<a name="56562"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 13 04 11:45 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Please review and make any suggestions or corrections on this. Thanks in advance.
<br />

<br />
Ok Folks
<br />

<br />
So far we have a few potential people coming. The only clear commitments I have gotten are definite maybe's from raiding friends and some of the Oath of the Chosen people. I will be working tonight to make sure that Jessex has her OS key as well as hopefully find a druid who will work with me on the eye of zomm trick. 
<br />

<br />
The Normal Trakanon is a 3-day spawn who is supposedly killed regularly. Hopefully he won't be joining us for supper.
<br />

<br />
First we clear the Lair of Juggernauts and other named folks. This should be done in concert by a Monk/Bard combo methinks. 
<br />

<br />
The Undead Bard spawns approximately every 18+/- hours.
<br />

<br />
Upon conversing with the Undead Bard and doing the turn-in / return, the Undead Bard will begin beating on me. Once he is killed, the &quot;undead&quot;(not really undead folks) Trakanon (aka Trak 2.0) will immediately spawn and aggro. 
<br />

<br />
For the Undead Bard fight, leave the casters out of it. Let only melee fight the undead bard. Then as soon as Trak spawns, Melee engage and only about 1 second later all casters unleash. 
<br />

<br />
The first thing Trak 2.0 will do is banish the first person with aggro. If we do not have a CotH Mage then that person will either have to run back from the Mushroom Forest or take one for the team. I am thinking a Bard with Fading Memories can do this, but am not sure. 
<br />

<br />
Here's my take on the fight.
<br />

<br />
Bard / Leader Reference:
<br />

<br />
Song's to mem are and be sung with drum are:
<br />

<br />
Warsong of Zek - For us unhasted folks without and epic. Add Reverse Damage Shield from Cleric on MA and SA
<br />

<br />
If only bard in Raid Purifying Chorus AE MR/PR/DR Resist. Highest level Bard covers this if not enough to cover all groups. Any additional Bard debuffs Trak and tries to land Fufil's, plus hastes and additional MR
<br />

<br />
If each group has a bard, then everyone should sing Psalm of Veeshan.
<br />

<br />
Call of Muse for Nuker's and DoTters adds 15% focus effect also allows for 30% overhaste on melee. 
<br />

<br />
Occlusion of Sound or Harmony of Sound to debuff Trak.
<br />

<br />
Aria of Asceticism to remove the nasty DoT from casters, especially healers. Everyone needs to make a &quot;/g I'm DoTted&quot; key for us to target and twist in Aria. Another key for &quot;/g I'm Cured&quot; might be helpful.
<br />

<br />
Kazumi's for Divine Aura on initial Bard (Lead Bard only) pull of Trak (someone said it will eliminate first banish, same true for Pally). Also have Deftdance Disc ready, then Puretone Disc.
<br />

<br />
Largo's Absonent Binding - If it will land, further snare and debuff the bugger
<br />

<br />
Group Consistancy:
<br />

<br />
Group 1
<br />

<br />
Lead Bard
<br />
3 - Tank Types, 2-Tanks with Monk for the tag pulling possibly
<br />
1 - Healer
<br />
1 - Mage, if possible, otherwise a Nuker
<br />

<br />
Group 2
<br />

<br />
Additional Bard, if possible
<br />
2 - Tank Types
<br />
1 - Healer
<br />
2 - Nukers
<br />

<br />
Group 3
<br />
Additional DPS, Hasted with Resists maxed
<br />

<br />
Trak is supposedly Unslowable so CHing MA and SA will be a must. Casters must conserve Mana for Trak, thus they should allow Tanks to handle UDB as stated previously. 
<br />

<br />
Rangers/Druids should land snare as soon as possible. Bards, Chanters and / or Shammies need to keep him debuffed and nuke when possible.
<br />

<br />
If the fight lasts more than a minute, we're in trouble.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Here is a Strategy from House of Kindred found online.
<br />

<br />
&quot;Now for the BardTrakanon Strategy!
<br />

<br />
First, making groups. We will set 2 tank types (SK/Palis) and 1 healer as a &quot;prewave&quot; to set off his first AOE. Also, it would nice to have a mage in the prewave group. The rest of the groups should be a normal trak raid.
<br />

<br />
Second, we will clear the entire room first. Pull the prot, grab tola, grab the juggs. If we aren't ready, wait and repull the juggs so that you're SURE they won't pop during the trak fight.
<br />

<br />
Third, have the prewave sit at the undead bard (leave the mage with your other casters, not at trak's pop spot). I will run over, hand in my lute, then HAUL back to the cove across the bridge, back the way you came. You should kill the undead bard out of range of trak. He should be pretty easy, but we need to make sure the pre-wave remains at the spawn point.
<br />

<br />
Once the undead bard dies, trak will pop at the undead bard's spawn point, not where we kill him. The pre-wave should be ready.
<br />

<br />
Fourth, the prewave will shout when the first AOE is off. Tanks will move across the bridge right when the undead bard dies, so they're ready to attack trak. When the first AOE goes off, tanks and clerics move forward. Mage will CotH whoever got ported to the shrooms. 
<br />

<br />
Fifth, after the next AOE, call you casters forward to nuke. Enchatner will Tash and Highest Druid/Ranger will snare Trak.
<br />

<br />
The entire thing should take about 30seconds to a minute.
<br />

<br />
_________
<br />

<br />
Make sure to bring your Poison Resist Gear -- the more you have the better - his aoe is 1200 dd and a LONG high damage dot, which is either full hit or full resist.
<br />

<br />
As soon as the undead bard is engaged all casters will stand, and remain standing until trakanon is dead -&quot;
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance
<br />

<br />
Wila...</span></td>
