				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Amateur Trak Homework to be graded and corrected please<a name="56876"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 16 04 9:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">casters must be under Trak to land a spell</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I couldn't agree with gabrielma more.  If somebody came to me and said, &quot;Treeb, if there's one single thing, and ONLY one single thing you could tell somebody that's planning a raid on Trakanon, what would it be?&quot;, I would tell them, &quot;Tell your casters to get into melee range to cast their spells, otherwise they will NOT land!&quot;.
<br />

<br />
The ONLY reason my first attempt at Fake Trak failed (for epic) is because I forgot about the melee-range thing for casters, and subsequently failed to tell the casters.  Most of the casters there had never fought Old World/Kunark dragons before, and didn't know about the melee-range casting.  We still (on that first attempt) got Trak down to about 9% with just melee damage and one wizzie nuking (he {wizzie} knew about the melee-range thing and was standing under Trak).  It still wasn't QUITE enough, though, and we wiped.  There were SEVERAL other DPS casters that NEVER landed a single spell in that fight, one of which was another wizzie.
<br />

<br />
A couple days later, we went back for a re-match and I told the casters about the melee-range casting requirement.  We smoked that hoser (Trak) down QUICK!
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
